text_answer.content: While I love these two passages, they may be a little complicated for 7th graders that are lower level readers. This is not necessarily a topic that they are familiar with as much as the topics about animals, for example, are familiar. The writing prompt asking for at least 6 key events may be a bit much even for 7th grade.  NOTE: maybe make them use 4 facts on the timeline instead. Some of the facts listed may be a little bit subtle for a 7th grader to know to use in their timeline (i.e. use of pea protein as well as beet juice may not be something they see to use in a "timeline"). I would place this later in the curriculum and maybe even make some of these facts a little more "obvious" or associated with a "time" so that they know how to use in a timeline.

text_answer.content: Just a comment on the writing assignment...one page could be long given the amount of time in a tutoring session. However, it could be done if the assignment was spread out over two sessions. Stating one page could just seem to be long for this grade given the time constraints. (Stating number of paragraphs instead of one page may seem more manageable as has been stated in other writing passages). However, I like how the required elements for the writing are outlined so they know exactly what we are looking for.
